@int03h The recommended only way to build bitcoin for windows, is through gitian. This also makes sure that people test the gititan descriptors, and thus that the releases make sense.
I don't understand how gitian 'impedes ability to replicate builds easily'. The _whole point_ of gitian is to make the results byte-by-byte deterministic so that they can be replicated.

@gavinandresen Sure, I'd like to help setting that up.
